# Etihad Interiors Theme v1.1.0 - Freeze Marker (rolled forward)

This file is the authoritative freeze marker for v1.1.0.
Until something changes it, the codebase's freeze boundaries are:

## Frozen manifest

What this freeze covers:

  - `src/app/**` (existing routes and components stay as-shipped)
  - `src/components/**` (existing public + admin widgets stay as-shipped)
  - `src/lib/**` (db, schema, auth, license, blob adapter, media, settings, pages, i18n, initDb)
  - `src/cms/blocks/**` (block registry, page-renderer, types)
  - `scripts/migrate.mjs` (idempotent schema migrations, tenants + tenant_data addition is part of v1.1.0)
  - `scripts/seed-pages.mjs` (seed content; string edits only for white-label pass)
  - `scripts/verify-deploy.mjs` (gates; additive only)
  - `vercel.json`
  - `next.config.mjs`

## Operator carve-out (added to v1.1.0)

The v1.1.0 release introduces operator surfaces that are **not** under the
buyer-visible freeze. These files can be added or edited to support the
superadmin console and Envato onboarding without breaking the buyer promise:

  - `src/app/superadmin/**` (operator console pages)
  - `src/app/api/operator/**` (operator-only routes)
  - `src/app/api/envato/webhook/route.ts` (Envato purchase intake)
  - `src/components/operator/**` (operator-only components)
  - `src/lib/operator-store.ts` (operator data layer)
  - `src/lib/operator-auth.ts` (operator cookie session)
  - `src/lib/tenant-brand.ts` (tenant brand + palette reader)

These surfaces are gated by `SUPERADMIN_EMAIL` + `SUPERADMIN_PASSWORD` env vars.
Buyers do not see them.

## Tenant carve-out (added to v1.1.0)

  - `scripts/apply-distro.mjs` (apply theme.distro.json to a tenant)
  - `data/theme.distro.json` (the studio demo distro override)
  - `data/studio-brand.json` (white-label fallback surface)
  - `docs/CONTEXT.md` (session continuity harness)
  - `data/tenants license + distro rows` (idempotent; re-running `npm run migrate` is the source)

## Documentation carve-out

What this freeze **does not cover**:

  - `CHANGELOG.md`, `OPERATOR.md`, `DEPLOY.md`, `INSTALL.md`, `README.md`, `SHIP.md`,
    `LICENSE.md`, `AGENT_BEST_PRACTICES.md`, `docs/feature-decisions.md` - documentation copy
  - `docs/CONTEXT.md` - session continuity harness
  - `docs/CLIENT_HANDOFF.md`, `docs/OPERATOR_QUICKREF.md`, `docs/SALES_NOTES.md`,
    `docs/envato-sales-brief.md`, `docs/theme-distro.schema.md`,
    `docs/theme-distro.example.json`, `docs/thumbs/v110/**`
  - `.env.example`, `.env.local.example`
  - `FREEZE-MARKER` (this file)
  - `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`

## Why the carve-out exists

v1.0.0 was sold as a buyer-complete artifact. v1.1.0 adds:

  - a superadmin console for the studio + Envato onboarding
  - a tenant model + theme.distro.json overlay
  - white-label-friendly defaults so the same codebase serves multiple studios

The buyer's rendered site (any GET on `/`, `/projects`, `/journal`, `/install`,
`/admin`) stays in the v1.0.0 contract. The operator surfaces live behind
gated auth and the buyer can never reach them.

